<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Inspects Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, today
urged Fujian, a coastal province in east China, to break away with
outmoded conventions impeding the development of the productive
forces and make bold experiment to promote economic development.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to implement the ideological policy of seeking
truth from facts in materializing the strategic objective set by
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
Tian said while winding up his tour of Fujian today.
</P>
<P>
Tian visited Fuzhou, Ningde, Xiamen and Zhangzhou cities from
November 8 to 18 in the company of Chen Mingyi, secretary of the
CPC Fujian Provincial Committee, and provincial governor He
Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
During his four-day tour of the eastern part of Fujian, which
was a revolutionary base area and is still economically
under-developed, Tian travelled over 1,000 km to make a
house-to-house visit in three cities and a county.
</P>
<P>
He urged local people to be market-oriented and integrate
agriculture with industry and commerce to catch up with other
regions in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
