<HEADLINE> FIFA Delay Fans Violence Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 18 (Xinhua) -- England's Football Association
(FA) announced that world football's governing body FIFA had
postponed their report on the fans violence during England's World
Cup qualifier against Italy in Rome last month until December 2.
</P>
<P>
FA chief executive Graham Kelly had asked FIFA to investigate
the crowd violence which occurred in a stand of the Olympic
Stadium reserved for England fans.
</P>
<P>
Italian police with batons rushed into England supporters.
</P>
<P>
The FA opened specail hot-lines to enble fans to recount what
they had experienced and then issued a report based on their
testimonies.
</P>
<P>
The report siad the Italian authorities had been gulty of "
deliberate intimidation and sometimes extreme provocation". It
also claimed that many England fans have been treated
intolerably. 
</P>
</TEXT>
