<HEADLINE> China Lists 166 Technological Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The State Economic and Trade
Commission made public a list of 166 state-level technological
development projects today in a pamphlet -- "Guide to China's Key
Technological Development Projects in 1996-2000 Period."
</P>
<P>
All the 166 projects chosen by the commission will be blessed
with the central government's financial support during the four
years, said Li Rongrong, vice-minister of the commission.
</P>
<P>
These projects represent 18 industries ranging from power
generation, petroleum, transportation, telecommunications,
metallurgy, electronics to medicine.
</P>
<P>
Included are the wind-driven electricity generation
technology, oil engineering in desert, digital picture for medical
use, CDMA (code diversion multiple accesses) communications
system and GPS (global positioning system) navigation equipment.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Lu'an, director of the technology and equipment
department of the commission, said that the funding of the 166
projects will be guaranteed with top priority in the country's
technological development cause.
</P>
<P>
Some of the technologies covered by the priority list could be
put into large-scale production in near future, he said.
</P>
<P>
These projects are only accessible for 512 state-owned
enterprises and 120 enterprise groups and will receive direct
financial support from government departments. The undertakers
will be chosen through a bidding here, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the state government sponsored the launch of 1,384
kinds of new products, which will generate sales revenues of 180
billion yuan and pre-taxed profits of 36 billion yuan over the
trial production period in 1996-1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
