<HEADLINE> US Computer company Chooses UK for Euro-Headquarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 18 (Xinhua) - American business software
specialist Computer Associates International is to base its 100
million pounds (160 million US dollars) state-of-the-art European
headquarters at Datchet, England.
</P>
<P>
The new headquarters is expected to generate hundreds of jobs
and will be a center for training and software development
excellence across Europe, Department of Trade and Industry (DTI)
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the decision, DTI Minister of State Ian McCartney
said that it confirms Britain's "preeminence in advanced
technology".
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the new headquarters will be the hub of
Computer Associates' operations, finance and research and
development within the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Opening in autumn 1999, the campus-style headquarters will be
managed with the company's Unicenter TNG enterprise management
software.
</P>
<P>
Computer Associates has a worldwide staff of 10,000 in 160
offices and enjoyed revenues of 4 billion US dollars in the 1997
fiscal year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
