<HEADLINE> Angola Urges Strengthening of Sanctions on UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Foreign Minister of
Angola Joao Miranda today urged African countries to join
together to implement the United Nations resolution on imposing
sanctions against the opposition UNITA.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while meeting African diplomats based in
Angola here today.
</P>
<P>
Miranda noted that some African countries still feel
resentment at implementing the UN sanctions against the National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
He said that such resentment should be criticized and
contained, otherwise the full implementation of the UN resolution
would be out of the question.
</P>
<P>
But Miranda said that imposing sanctions against the
UNITA does not mean to exclude it from the political life of
Angola. The government holds that the UNITA is part of the
national politics system, he added.
</P>
<P>
The UN resolution on sanctions against the UNITA took effect on
October 30. 
</P>
