<DOCNO> XIE19971119.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECA Observes African Statistics and Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Theme of this year's
African satatistics and information days, which fall on Novemebr
18 and 19, is ''building an inforamtion society'', the United
Nations Economic Commission for Africa (ECA) said today.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued here, the ECA said the observation
of the African statistics and information days this year is
centered around strengthening statistical information systems,
promoting information technologies, building geoinformation
systems and dissemination of development information.
</P>
<P>
The ECA said the weak status of national statistical services
was recognized by the ECA conference of ministers responsible for
economic and social development which adopted the Addis Ababa
Plan of Action for statistical development in Africa and the
strategy for its implementation.
</P>
<P>
Through the Coordinating Committee on African Statistical
Development (CASD), a task force on connectivety for statistics
was established in May 1997 to ensure that CASD members and
eventually national statistical services are connected through
the Internet, the ECA said. This will enable coordination and
speedier transfer of data between or among countries, ECA and
other international agencies, it added.
</P>
<P>
It said the African focal point for this effort, the ECA's
Development Inforamtion Services Division, is charged with the
responsibility of coordinating and implementating the African
Information Society Initiative (AISI), a framework for putting in
place a development-centered inforamtion society adopted by the
ministers in 1996.
</P>
<P>
This year's commemoration of the African statistics and
information days, offers an opportunity for individuals and
organizations within African countries#,international
organizations, donor agencies and the mass media "to assist in
enhancing inforamtion infrastructure, as well as data production
and dissemination for effective socio-economic policy analysis
and management'', the ECA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
