<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Rocks Southwestern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake today
rocked Patras, a city in the southwestern Greek Peloponnese
peninsula and the nearby Ionian island of Zakinthos, but causing
minor damage to farms and shops.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 6.6 on the richter scale occurred at
around 15:12 pm local time with its epicentre being located in the
sea bed south of Zakynthos, 290 km southwestern of Athens, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
George Stavrakais, director of Athens Geodynamic Institute,
said today that another earthquake measuring 6.0 richter also
shocked the same areas at 15:13 pm local time.
</P>
<P>
Strong aftershocks might be expected, he added. 
