<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Visiting British Secretary of
State for Energy and Science John Battle today urged more efforts
to be put into cooperation in oil tapping between his country and
Angola.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks here at a symposium on deep water
technology held by British Petroleum Corporation (BP).
</P>
<P>
Britain could offer Angola the technology and experience in
deep-water oil tapping, he said.
</P>
<P>
