<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran today condemned the
Israel's secretive nuclear weapon program and the massacre of
tourists in Egypt's historical relic of Luxor, the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi was
quoted as saying that the possession by the Israeli government of
atomic weapons betrays their belligerent intentions and their
hatred of peace and security.
</P>
<P>
Former Israeli Prime Minister Shimon Perez told the Japanese
daily Yomyuri Shimbon earlier this week that Tel Aviv's
possession of atomic weapons promotes regional peace, and deters
wars.
</P>
<P>
It is ironical that the Middle East countries consider atomic
disarmament as an element contributing to peace while Israel
recognizes peace as the fruit only of its possession of that
destructive weapon, Mohammadi said.
</P>
<P>
He said it was shameful that an Israeli official frankly
admits that Israeli has atomic arsenals while the same regime has
raised a hue and cry intentionally lodging irrelevant claims
against Iran with the idea of leading international conscience
away from its own atomic weapons.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi condemned the massacre of tourists in Egypt Monday
morning, saying that in the Islamic view the ominous phenomenon of
terrorism and killing innocent persons is a condemnable wretched
act.
</P>
<P>
Six gunmen shot randomly at tourists, killing 77 and wounding
at least 24. 
