<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The ministers of finance,
foreign affairs and the federal capital territory have survived
the cabinet dissolution by the Nigerian military regime.
</P>
<P>
In his nationwide speech to mark the fourth anniversary of the
military regime on Monday, General Sani Abacha, Nigeria's head of
state, announced the dissolution of the cabinet with immediate
effect.
</P>
<P>
However, the three ministers were not affected, said Alhaji
Gidado Idris, secretary to the Government of the Federation
today.
</P>
<P>
