respective permanent secretaries all government property, such as
cars and cellular telephones, Idris was quoted by a Nigerian
Television Authority report as saying.
</P>
<P>
Security has been beefed up substantially at the Federal
Secretariat following the dissolution of the Federal Executive
Council, or cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Armed soldiers and policemen who have taken over the
secretariat security arrangement are seen searching thoroughly
the booths of every car that drove out of the complex.
</P>
<P>
Although the security operatives refused to make comments on
the sudden reinforcement, observers noted that the new
arrangement has something to do with the prevention of possible
removal of government property by either the departing officials
or their numerous agents and aides. 
