<HEADLINE> Somalia Appeals for Emergency Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Somalia today appealed to
the international community, U.N. agencies, donor countries and
non-governmental organizations to provide emergency relief to the
flood affected Somalis in southern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here by the National Salvation Council
of Somalia (NSC) said the unprecedented torrential rains followed
by floods have killed hundreds of Somalia in addition to
destroying crops and harvest stores.
</P>
<P>
But U.N. agencies said over 2,000 have died because of the
floods resulting from heavy rains since mid-October in Southern
Somalia. Two major rivers have burst their banks and hundreds of
villages were submerged in flood waters.
</P>
<P>
The press release said, many more death tolls are expected as
a result of malaria, diarrhea and other epidemic diseases
triggered by the reported natural calamities.
</P>
<P>
The NSC which comprises 25 Somali factions now meeting in
Addis, said, ''the valleys of Shabelle and Juba are the areas
most affected with more than one million people left homeless.''
</P>
