squadrons of 33 Mirage 2000 fighters it bought from France 11
years ago to make them capable of launching air-to-air and
air-to-ground missiles and equipped with electronic war means,
said Mubarek.
</P>
<P>
French companies, including the Dassault Aviation group which
makes Mirage fighters, are strongly present at the International
Aeronautics and Armament Saloon being held in Dubai, one of the
emirates of UAE, from November 16. 
