<HEADLINE> Spanish Climber Overcomes Mt. Cho Oyu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 19 (Xinhua) -- A member of Spain's Glacia
Desafi Expedition scaled the 8,201-meter Mt. Cho Oyu on November 6,
Nepal's Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation said today.
</P>
<P>
Martinez Novas Jesus overcame the peak, the sixth highest in the
world, via the southwest ridge.
</P>
<P>
He spent 10 minutes on the summit before returning to the third
camp. 
</P>
