<HEADLINE> Pak Chief of Army Staff Calls on PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Chief of Army Staff of
Pakistan General Jahangir Karamat called on Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif here today, informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
Karamat discussed with Sharif the current political situation
in the country with special reference to the relations between the
government and the judiciary, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, Karamat returned home this morning
from the United Kingdom, cutting short his foreign visit, in view
of the prevailing situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the confrontation between the government and the
judiciary intensified as the Parliament adopted the amended
contempt law tending to give protection to Sharif in the ongoing
case of contempt against him in the Supreme Court of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The amended law came only one day after Sharif declined to
tender an apology in the Supreme Court in the contempt of court
case against him.  
</P>
</TEXT>
