<HEADLINE> Fifty Candidates to Contest Euro Footballer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 19 (Xinhua) -- A total of 50 famous players
have been named by organisers France Football magazine as
candidates for this year's European Footballer of the Year award.
</P>
<P>
Germans including 1997 winner Matthias Sammer, Juergen
Kohler, Andreas Moeller and Karl-Heinz Riedle are among the
candidates.
</P>
<P>
There are six members of the Juventus side beaten by Borussia,
including Frenchmen Zinedine Zidane and Didier Deschamps and
Italian striker Christian Vieri, now with Atletico Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Other Italians in the list include Chelsea's Gianfranco Zola,
Alessandro Del Piero, Enrico Chiesa and Filippo Inzaghi.
</P>
<P>
After Liberian George Weah in 1995, the trophy could go to a
non-European for the second time in three years with Brazilian
Ronaldo of Inter Milan, runner-up to Sammer and FIFA's reigning
world player of the year, the favourite.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo heads a group of six Brazilians including the
Spanish based Rivaldo, Sonny Anderson, Juninho and Roberto
Carlos and veteran former Brazil captain Rai of Paris St
Germain.
</P>
<P>
Weah, third in the FIFA poll in January, is not among the 50
after a poor year for his club AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
Following are the 50 competitors with clubs, country:
</P>
<P>
Sonny Anderson - Monaco, Barcelona, Brazil
</P>
<P>
Krassimir Balakov - VfB Stuttgart, Bulgaria
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Batistuta - Fiorentina, Argentina
</P>
<P>
David Beckham - Manchester United, England
</P>
<P>
Dennis Bergkamp - Arsenal, Netherlands
</P>
<P>
Oliver Bierhoff - Udinese, Germany
</P>
<P>
Laurent Blanc - Barcelona, Olympique Marseille, France
</P>
<P>
Enrico Chiesa - Parma, Italy
</P>
<P>
Hernan Crespo - Parma, Argentina
</P>
<P>
Ivan de la Pena - Barcelona, Spain
</P>
<P>
Alessandro Del Piero - Juventus, Italy
</P>
<P>
Didier Deschamps - Juventus, France
</P>
<P>
Youri Djorkaeff - Inter Milan, France
</P>
<P>
Ciro Ferrara - Juventus, Italy
</P>
<P>
Luis Figo - Barcelona, Portugal
</P>
<P>
Robbie Fowler - Liverpool, England
</P>
<P>
Ryan Giggs - Manchester United, Wales
</P>
</TEXT>
