<HEADLINE> Goodyear to Stop Supplying Formula One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- American company Goodyear
will stop its tyre supply to the Formular One teams since the end
of the 1998 season.
</P>
<P>
The tyre giant has taken a lion's share in the Formular One
field and its customers include the Williams, the reigning world
champions, and Ferrari.
</P>
<P>
Last season another tyre supplier Bridgestone of Japan began
defying Goodyear by supplying several Formula One teams.
</P>
<P>
Formula One sources said that French company Michelin will take
the place of Goodyear. 
</P>
</TEXT>
