<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Approves 18 Projects at 862M Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of the
Bangladeshi National Economic Council today approved 18 projects
at an estimated cost of over 38.62 billion taka (about 862 million
U.S. dollars), the national news agency BSS reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The projects include the construction of railway on Bangabandhu
Bridge, power distribution projects in 18 towns, Dhaka-Aricha
highway development and rehabilitation project, reconstruction of
five bridges on the Dhaka-Chittagong national highway, a project
for reducing traffic jam in Dhaka under the crash program and the
development and repair of different important roads in Dhaka
metropolitan city, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The cost of seven projects will be funded by local resources,
BSS added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
