<HEADLINE> Telecommunications Products Trade Center Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Telecommunications
Products Trade Center of China officially opened today in the
Pudong New Area, a booming trade and financial zone in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The center, with 44 members, will provide a nationwide market
for telecommunications products manufactured in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The center entered trial operations in October 1995. Its total
sales volume through the end of October this year hit 2.3 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The center plans that the volume will top two billion yuan in
1998 alone. 
</P>
