<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Western China Investment Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, November 19 (Xinhua) -- A national seminar on investment
and exploration in central and western China opened today in
Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The Special Economic Zone Office of the State Council, State
Science and Technology Commission and Hubei Province are jointly
sponsoring the four-day seminar.
</P>
<P>
Central and western China are home to over 60 percent of the
nation's population, 85 percent of total land, 60 percent of
mineral reserves and 90 percent of water resources.
</P>
<P>
The seminar has attracted over 400 representatives from 38
trade missions in 14 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from Shaanxi, Sichuan, Henan, Anhui, Hubei,
Jiangxi and Hunan provinces and Chongqing Municipality will brief
participants on their respective investment environments.
</P>
<P>
Various industrialists, bankers and experts from the World Bank
and the United Nations Industrial Development Organization will
report on measures central and western regions have introduced to
attract foreign investment, and on emerging trends and challenges
facing developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
