<HEADLINE> Chaozhou Natives Society Holds Annual Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The International Society of
Chaozhou Natives held its ninth annual meeting today in Shantou,
one of China's five special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, attended the opening
ceremony along with other dignitaries, including Xie Fei,
secretary of the Guangdong Committee of the Communist Party of
China, and Ka-shing Li, chairman of Cheung Kong (Holding) Co.,
Ltd, of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the first of its kind held on China's mainland,
attracted more than 3,000 Chaozhou natives from 24
countries. Eight annual meetings since 1981 were held in Hong
Kong, Malaysia, Singapore, Macao, France and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Xu Lide, honorary chairman of the annual meeting, noted more
than 10 million Chaozhou natives currently live overseas. He said
cooperation and exchanges between Chaozhou and other parts of the
world have greatly enhanced ties between natives.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the society is to strengthen ties between natives
and promote the traditional culture of Chaozhou, a commercial and
maritime hub since ancient China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
