<HEADLINE> Iranian Ambassadors to Return to European </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced today to
return its ambassadors to the member states of the European
Union (EU) as of today, but saying that ties with the EU
countries would not be at the same level.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, Iranian
deputy foreign minister for Euro-American affairs Morteza Sarmadi
said that the first group of Iranian ambassadors would leave
here today for their missions in the EU countries.
</P>
<P>
Iran's ambassador to Rome, Italy Majid Hedayatzadeh is to be
the first Iranian ambassador to leave for his assignment today,
the IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
However, Sarmadi noted that grounds for joint cooperation and
the understanding of the EU countries about the realities in
Iran especially after coming into office of the new Iranian
government determine the level of Iran's ties with them.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the bad performance of certain countries, Iran
has developed a negative mentality about them and about
continuation of long-term relations with them, he said, adding
that they must strive in the future to correct their picture.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Iran and the EU countries were cooled down
with the EU envoys to Tehran recalled after the Berlin court
ruled that Iranian leaders were behind the 1992 assassination of
four Iranian rebel Kurdish leaders in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Most of the EU envoys returned to Tehran Friday morning after
the two sides reached an agreement.
</P>
<P>
Referring to future relations between Iran and the EU,
Sarmadi stated that Iran would regard cooperation with Europe as
a principled policy provided that they guarantee reciprocal
respect and interests.
</P>
<P>
The level of Tehran-EU cooperation in future depends on the
role Europe will play at the international fora, he said, adding
that Europe cannot ignore Iran's strategic location in the
region and its role and influence in the world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
An "independent Europe" is of importance to Iran, he
stressed, in case Europe favors an independent role and not a
subordinate one, new areas will emerge for their cooperation
with Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
