<HEADLINE> Foiled Coup Plot Against S. Leonean Junta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, November 19 (xinhua) -- The Sierra Leonean military
junta today confirmed that it has foiled a coup plot hatched by
about 10 people including Steve Bio, a businessman, and Colonel
Gibril Massaquoi, spokesman of the rebel Revolutionary United
Front (RUF).
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua, Secretary-General of the
military government Sesay said, "yee, we nipped the affair in the
bud and both men are now detained in the capital."
</P>
<P>
He said about eight others including some military officers
are also being held while a probe into the affair is being
conducted by both the police and the Department of Defence.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more details of the plot were revealed by
intelligence sources in Freetown today.
</P>
<P>
Both men were arrested in Kenema on Sunday morning in the east
of the country by the RFU Battle Field Commander Issa Sesay.
</P>
<P>
"They have been busy over the weekend trying to persuade RUF
youths to ignore the disarmament program (slated to begin on
December 1 )," one source said.
</P>
<P>
The source said that RUF number two man, Colonel Sam Bockari
who was also approached on the plot declined to take part, saying
"we have been ordered to take instructions from Major Koroma (the
Sierra Leone Leader) by Corporal Foday Sankoh and no one else."
</P>
<P>
It said Bockari dismissed Bio's claim that he had been
mandated by Corporal Sankoh to carry out the coup plot.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed reports said that Bio, a high profile businessman,
has a large quantity of arms and ammunition deposited in Banjul.
</P>
<P>
Up to 15 people have been picked up from various parts of the
country and brought down to the Maximum Security Prison in the
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
