<TEXT>
<P>
Lim, who replaced Kang Kyong-shik as new deputy prime minister
for financial and economic affairs today, told a news conference
this afternoon that the government "will seek assistance from the
IMF, if only necessary."
</P>
<P>
He said his new economic policy team will strive to solve the
foreign currency crunch at local financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
