<HEADLINE> Macao Foreign Exchange Reserve Reaches Record Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Macao's reserve of foreign
exchange reached 20.5 billion patacas (2.59 billion US dollars) by
the end of August, the highest record in history.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the Macao Currency and Foreign Exchange
Supervisory Department show that the growth of Macao's foreign
exchange reserve was not affected by international speculation on
Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the amount of currency in circulation in broad sense (M2),
53 percent was Hong Kong dollars while Macao patacas accounted for
31 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government recorded a fiscal surplus of 919
million patacas (about 116.3 million US Dollars) during the first
nine months of the year, up 29.8 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
About 90 percent of the revenue increase came from tax on
casinos.
</P>
<P>
In addition, expenditures also rose 8.5 percent between January
and September.  
</P>
</TEXT>
