<HEADLINE> Motion Backing PM Tabled in Malaysian Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 19 (Xinhua) -- A motion expressing full
support for Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad was tabled
in Parliament here today.
</P>
<P>
The motion tabled by Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim also
voiced objection to the United States' investigations into the
country's national oil corporation Petronas' investment in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The motion was tabled in the House of Representatives here
following a draft resolution by some U.S. congressmen demanding
Mahathir to publicly apologize or resign over his alleged
statement of a Jewish conspiracy in recent Southeast Asian
currency speculation.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir has repeatedly clarified that his remarks were
misinterpreted and that he is not anti-Jew.
</P>
<P>
The motion states that Malaysia is a sovereign and independent
nation whose development is based on democracy and consensus, that
the relations with other countries must adhere to the principle of
justice, freedom, equality and respect for one another.
</P>
<P>
It also states that Malaysia gives its citizens the freedom to
choose their own leader and government through the process of a
free and democratic election and that Malaysia practices the
principle of free trade.
</P>
<P>
The motion regrets the effort made by the U.S. government to
use the Iran-Libya Sanctions Act on Petronas for investing in the
gas industry in Iran.
</P>
<P>
It says that Malaysia will uphold the principle of harmonious
living of the various races and religions and it will continue
under the leadership of Mahathir. And in accordance with the fair,
just and open policy that is being practiced, it refutes the
statement that the national leaders of the country are
anti-Semitic or against any other races.
</P>
<P>
It objects the motion by several U.S. congressmen for their
baseless allegation and their dispute on the sovereignty and the
right of the people and asks the international community to
respect the rights of the people of any nation to determine their
own leadership and national policies through the process of
democracy and consensus.
</P>
<P>
The motion says Malaysia strives to ensure the continuity of
good relations with the U.S. in all aspects and to enhance such
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
