<HEADLINE> Somali Flood Victims Receive First Significant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- People in the flood
affected area of Somalia have received their first significant
aid in weeks, a report reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the International Committee of the Red Cross
as saying that about 7,500 people in Beletwin, a key trading
center in central Somalia have received blankets.
</P>
<P>
About 26 tons of biscuits have arrived in Mogadishu from the
Kenyan capital Nairobi and will be distributed in Beletwin.
</P>
<P>
The international aid agency, Care, said the death toll in flood
affected areas have risen to more than 1,260 and up to 250,000
people have been displaced.
</P>
<P>
International efforts to provide relief aid are limited so far
because airstrips have been flooded in the areas. But aid
agencies say they have now obtained four helicopters to help them
in rescue operations, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
