<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets Raul Castro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met today with
Raul Castro, first vice-president of the Council of State and
Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, recalled his visit to Cuba in January this year, and
noted that he was deeply impressed with the Communist Party of Cuba
and the fact that the Cuban people strictly adhere to the socialist
road and harbor deep feelings of friendship for the CPC and
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed delight at once again meeting Castro, and the
two leaders exchanged views on issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
He said the Communist Party of Cuba and the Cuban people have
stood the severe test of time and overcome various difficulties
despite the rapidly changing and increasingly complicated
international situation since the end of the 1980s. He also pointed
out that the Cuban people have recorded satisfactory achievements in
building their motherland and promoting the socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
"China admires the nation's success," said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He said the CPC treasures the friendship and cooperative ties
between the two countries and two parties, and noted that China
will continue to support the just cause of the Communist Party of
Cuba and the efforts of the Cuban people to safeguard state
sovereignty and national independence, and adhere to socialism.
</P>
<P>
China is fully prepared to strengthen friendship and
cooperative ties in order to promote the comprehensive development
of relations between the two countries, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed Castro on the highly successful 15th National
Congress of the CPC and efforts to build the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Castro noted that in-depth exchange of views on Sino-Cuban ties
and other issues of common concern has been highly beneficial.
</P>
<P>
He said the Cuban delegation will visit a number of cities to
survey China's success in reform, opening up and economic
construction, and expressed the hope to learn more about the
country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that his visit will further advance
friendship and cooperative relations between the two nations and
two parties. He added that the visit will also promote the
development of mutually beneficial trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Castro also briefed Hu on the Fifth National Congress of the
Communist Party of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Castro placed a wreath at the Monument for the
People's Heroes in central Beijing. 
</P>
