<HEADLINE> Fmr. Deputy-Commander of Jinan Military Area Command Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Teng Haiqing, former
deputy-commander of the Jinan Military Area Command of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army which is one of China's seven regional
military commands, passed away on October 28 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Teng, 88, a veteran communist who joined the Red Army in 1930,
participated in the Long March (1934-1935) and numerous major
military campaigns, including the Anti-Japanese War (1937-1945)
and War of Liberation (1945-1949). Teng was promoted to the rank
of lieutenant general in 1955.
</P>
<P>
Teng also served as a deputy to Eighth National Congress of the
CPC and member of Ninth CPC Central Committee.  
</P>
