<HEADLINE> East China Province Leads in Saving Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 19 (Xinhua) -- China's Shandong province has
saved 13.3 billion yuan (1.6 billion US dollars) through its
energy saving projects since 1991.
</P>
<P>
This amount is equal to 50 percent of the profits of industrial
enterprises in the province in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Shandong, which is rich in energy resources, was one of the
first provinces to set different rates for electricity depending
on the period of use and popularized the use of energy-saving
lightbulbs. These two measures can save 5 billion kwh of
electricity annually, accounting for around seven percent of the
total amount of electricity generated by the province last year.
</P>
<P>
Improved technology for fans and water pumps used in industry
has helped save 566 million kwh of electricity. A move to make the
public more energy-conscious has resulted in saving 2.2 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province has also strengthened legislature in the field of
energy saving. Since 1991, it has enacted 50 decrees, rule and
regulations in this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
