<DOCNO> XIE19971119.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plans to Achieve Zero Population Growth Rate by 2030 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- China plans to achieve a zero
population growth rate prior to the year 2030, with the population
standing at between 1.5 billion and 1.6 billion, according to
State Councillor Song Jian.
</P>
<P>
Song made the statement today at the ongoing '97 China
Environmental Forum. He noted that the first several decades of
the next century will be a crucial period for China's further
development.
</P>
<P>
Song noted that fulfilling the important task will enable
China, a densely populated and underdeveloped country with a weak
infrastructure, to achieve continued economic development and
further improve the living standards of its people.
</P>
<P>
"Economic growth is crucial, and must be achieved in
coordination with social and resource development and
environmental improvements," said Song, adding that China's goal
is to achieve sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Song said China will persist in regarding environmental
protection as a basic state policy and sustainable development as
the overall strategy guiding China's social and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Song expressed his firm belief that reaching the goal of a zero
population growth rate by 2030 will enable China to achieve
sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
China's population hit 1.223 billion by the end of last year,
with the massive population exerting great pressure on the
nation's resources, economic development and environmental
protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
China's introduction of the "One Child Policy" in 1980 has
effectively reduced the actual population growth by some 300
million. Extensive efforts by the Chinese government have reduced
the natural population growth rate to 10.42 per thousand.
</P>
<P>
China's current efforts to solve population problems center on
the introduction of comprehensive measures to improve education
and social security.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
