<HEADLINE> Ostersund's Bid for Winter Olympics Fails Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish Olympic
Committee frustrated Ostersund's fourth bid to host the 2006
Winter Olympics on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Olympic officials listed the lack of improvements in
its bid as the top reason they did not support the city.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic Committee also doubted that the city could win
support from business, the public and sports community.
</P>
<P>
Ostersund was narrowly edged by Lillehammer, Norway, in its
bid for the 1994 Games, and its bids for 1998 and 2002 lost
again. 
