<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dkaha Urged to Privatize Gas, Power Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Chamber of
Industries (BCI) has suggested that the government privatize the
gas and power sectors, BCI sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
This suggestion was made by BCI President Sharif Afzal Hossain
when a 41-member delegation headed by him called on Power, Energy
and Mineral Resources Minister Mohammad Nooruddin Khan Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Although there is a clear policy for privatization of these
sectors, privatization is being delayed due to administrative
complacence and lack of proper rules and regulations, the BCI
chief said, adding that as a result, domestic and foreign
investors feel discouraged to invest in these sectors.
</P>
<P>
The industrial and business sectors are the main users of
electricity and gas, he stated, "but production and business are
being seriously hampered due to load shedding and other problems."
</P>
<P>
Appreciating the government initiative for privatization, the
BCI chief said that the government should not only privatize the
industrial units but also play the role of watchdog in the
formulation of proper policies and their implementation.
</P>
<P>
The development of infrastructure is a must for the development
of energy, electricity and mineral resources sectors, he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister thanked the chamber leaders, saying that the
government was giving priority to the creation of suitable
infrastructure for gas and electricity sectors and that his
ministry is "a service-oriented institution which is always ready
to serve and improve the quality of service".
</P>
<P>
According to the directives of the prime minister, the whole of
Bangladesh has been divided into 23 blocks and gas exploration is
going on in these blocks to solve the problems in gas and
electricity sectors, the minister stated.
</P>
<P>
The minister also mentioned that the government had already
formulated a policy for electricity production in the private
sector and had started work in that direction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
