<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Fall Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices shed
modestly today by 0.89 percent to close at 10,154.36 points.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index fell 142 points in the first minute of
the opening today, and then slumped to 9,900 points before holding
its foot narrowly above the 10,000-point level at the midday
close.
</P>
<P>
Fear of rising interest rates cast a shadow over the market
sentiment, securities analysts said. The primary three-month
interbank lending rates climbed up 0.75 percent Tuesday to 11.5
percent amid concerns that the collapse of the South Korean
currency might put new pressure on the Hong Kong dollar.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, the blue-chip index recouped some of its lost
ground to close at the highest of the day, 10,154.36 points.
</P>
<P>
Property, bank, commerce and industry shares fell modestly
today, while utilities counters, H shares and red-chips went up
slightly.
</P>
<P>
Turnover continued to be slim, at about 8.2 billion HK dollars
(one billion US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
