<HEADLINE> US Secretary of State Cuts Short Visit to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright today cut short her visit to India and rushed
to Geneva to meet her British, French and Russian counterparts for
a diplomatic action on Iraq, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Albright, who canceled several engagements in New Delhi, had a
series of telephone conversation with foreign ministers of Russia,
Britain and France last night and this morning, U.S. State
Department spokesman James Rubin told reporters here.
</P>
<P>
She was also in constant touch with President Bill Clinton, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"As a result of those conversations, she is cutting short her
trip to India and fly to Geneva where she will be meeting with the
foreign ministers of Russia, Britain and France," Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. secretary of state, who arrived here last evening from
Islamabad on a two-day visit, today held formal talks with Indian
Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral.
</P>
<P>
