<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 19 (Xinhua) -- A five-member bench of the
Supreme Court today formally framed charges in contempt case
against Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, six parliamentarians, three
newspapers and Pakistan television.
</P>
<P>
The charge sheet against the prime minister was mainly based on
his reported press talk in parliament house on October 29 and his
address at Iqbal House in Lahore reported in the press on October
30.
</P>
<P>
The apex court asked Sharif and eleven other respondents
separately whether they plead guilty and have anything else to
say.
</P>
