that the chief justice has suspended 14th Amendment of the
Constitution without any authority in just one and a half days and
is responsible for bringing the country to unfortunate and
undemocratic situation.
</P>
<P>
The charge sheet quoted the prime minister as saying that the
chief justice had threatened to strike down the law passed by the
parliament regarding the strength of the Supreme Court judges if
it ran counter to the wishes of the apex court.
</P>
<P>
During the press talk, Sharif reportedly said that in spite of
his best efforts to resolve the crisis, "the Chief Justice struck
down the 14th Amendment to the Constitution which is illegal and
unconstitutional."
</P>
<P>
Referring to the speech at Iqbal House, the charge sheet stated
that Sharif made the statement that he respected the judiciary in
an "ironical manner" which resulted in a burst of laughter in the
audience." 
