<HEADLINE> China to Coordinate Economic Growth, Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- China will coordinate economic
development and environmental protection through better policies
and regional economic planning, said Hao Jianxiu, Vice-Minister in
charge of the State Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Hao offered her remarks here today at the '97 China
Environmental Forum.
</P>
<P>
She said that when making investment decisions more preferences
will be given to enterprises that help protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to increase investments in environmental
protection and improve the development of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Hao said great achievements have been made in coordinating
economic development and environmental protection since 1978, when
China began to implement a reform and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
From 1978 to 1996, China's Gross National Product more than
quadrupled, with an average annual growth rate of 9.9 percent, but
the increase in pollutants during the period remained much lower
than the economic growth rate, she said.
</P>
<P>
"For an economically weak country like China, this achievement
is really significant," she said.
</P>
<P>
Experience from some developed countries has shown that the
goal of sustainable economic development and a healthy environment
could be realized if effective measures were taken, Hao said.
</P>
<P>
She added that those cities with relatively better
environmental conditions in China were usually economically
developed ones, such as Zhuhai in Guangdong Province, Xiamen in
Fujian Province and Dalian in Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Governmental officials, representatives from international
organizations for environmental protection, experts
and entrepreneurs from more than 20 countries attended the four-day
forum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
