<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
fall on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index declined by another 8.04 points to close at
1680.97 points today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the share prices fell because investors were
pessimistic about prospects for the near term as regional economic
gloom shrouded the market.
</P>
<P>
