<HEADLINE> Disney Reports Record Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The Walt Disney Co. today
reported record revenues, operating income and earnings for both
the fourth quarter and fiscal year ended Sept.30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the same period last year, revenues for the fourth
quarter increased 5 percent to 5.5 billion U.S. dollars and
operating income increased 13 percent to 1 billion while net
income increased 18 percent to 411 million, according to a news
release from the company.
</P>
<P>
Revenues for the year increased 6 percent to 22.5 billion,
operating income for the year increased 18 percent to 4.3 billion
and net income increased 25 percent to 1.9 billion, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The entertainment giant said operating earnings rose 21 percent
at its creative content business, which includes movies, home
videos, The Disney Stores and merchandise licensing.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the worldwide performance of "Hercules" and the
U.S. success of "George," Disney cited strong U.S. video sales of
"Sleeping beauty" and "Pooh's Great Adventure."
</P>
<P>
Broadcasting earnings rose 18 percent on growth in subscribers
and advertising at its cable networks --the Disney Channel and
ESPN, which was purchased along with ABC.
</P>
<P>
Earnings from theme parks grew 15 percent as the 25th
anniversary of Walt Disney World Boosted tourism to offset reduced
attendance at Disneyland.
</P>
<P>
The strong theme park performance sets Disney on the right
footing for upcoming openings of new parks in fiscal 1998. The
company plans to open a fourth theme park at the Orlando resort,
Disney's Animal Kingdom in April and plans to start cruise ship
services in the late spring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
