<HEADLINE> Census: Mozambique Has 15.74 Million People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The preliminary result of the
national census shows that Mozambique has a population of 15.74
million, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The figure was released by Mozambique's national census office
Tuesday, according to the local daily Noticias.
</P>
<P>
The census conducted during August 1 and 15 this year,
indicates that there are four million more people in the country
now than the figure by the 1980 national census.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the country's population would have
reached 18.5 million by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Of the 11 provinces in the country, Zambezia and Nampula are
still the most populated provinces with 3.2 million and 3.06
million people respectively.
</P>
<P>
Niassa is the province with the smallest population of 764,000
people.
</P>
<P>
The capital city of Maputo has a population of one million,
not 1.7 million as people had generally estimated.
</P>
<P>
This is, however, only a preliminary result, the paper said,
adding that final result from the census would come out by
mid-1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
