<HEADLINE> Illegal Foreign Workers Asked to Leave Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Qatari Interior Ministry
has asked illegal expatriate workers to leave the country by
January 20 or face penalties, the Qatari News Agency (QNA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry gave no details in its statement carried by the
QNA, but it said "after the fixed periods expire, the concerned
authorities in the Interior Ministry will take stiff measures
against violators."
</P>
<P>
Qatar is the fifth Gulf Arab country to expel illegal aliens
after the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, Bahrain and
Kuwait. The countries are trying to control their labor markets
dominated by foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners in Qatar outnumber its natives. Official figures
show that of an estimated 650,000 people living there, only
about 160,000 are citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
