<BODY>
<HEADLINE> System Of Shareholders Benefits State-Owned Sector In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese economist said
here today that the system of shareholders will greatly help
state-owned enterprises and the state-owned sector as a whole,
making their overall performance better than that of other
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Gao Shangquan, vice-president of the Chinese Society for
Research on the Restructuring of the Economic System, told a
recent international seminar here that, since the 1980s, the
system of shareholders has shown that it has a role to play in
the Chinese economy and, together with the securities and capital
markets, will have a profound impact on the well-being of
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gao noted, there are still some problems around in
developing the system in China, like a lack of protection of
individual interests and the loss of state assets.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party officially endorsed the system as a viable
means of revitalizing the state-owned enterprises at the 15th
Party Congress held in September.
</P>
<P>
In addition to representatives of the State Commission for
Restructuring the Economy and the Development and Research Center
of the State Council, the seminar attracted representatives from
the World Bank, the IMF, the United States, Germany, Japan, France
and Poland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
