<HEADLINE> Qinghua University Awards Outstanding Postdoctoral Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Twenty postdoctoral students
won titles of "Outstanding Postdoctoral Students of Qinghua
University" here today. The ceremony celebrated a milestone for
the university: The total number of postdoctoral students has
exceeded 500.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University, a well-known engineering school, has
enrolled 523 postdoctoral students since 1985 when China first
introduced the postdoctoral system.
</P>
<P>
Postdoctoral students have become a vital force in the
university's research work.
</P>
<P>
Materials show that during the 1993-1996 period, 296
postdoctoral students undertook 284 state-level and 154
provincial-level research programs, helped popularize 43 items of
scientific achievements, which produced 13.34 million yuan (1.67
million U.S. dollars) in economic returns.
</P>
<P>
The students published 2,434 research papers and 33 books.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, 132 postdoctoral students remained at
the university as faculty members. 
</P>
