<HEADLINE> Northern Province Improves Plight of Low-Income Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in
northern China has established minimum-pay criteria for many
residents of both cities and townships.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang, capital of the province, was the pioneer in
guaranteeing local farmers a minimum monthly pay of 100 to 140
yuan in March of 1996. Since then, 159 other cities and counties
have followed suit. The annual per capita allotment averages 500
to 1,400 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Cities in the province also established measures to ensure
citizens a minimum of 120 to 140 yuan each month. This year, 6.4
million yuan has already been raised for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has accumulated a total premium of
36.99 million yuan for old-age pensions from 6.35 million farmers.
</P>
</TEXT>
