<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Workers Like Reading Books </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 19 (Xinhua) -- An ongoing book fair here
has attracted a great number of workers in the southern metropolis
of Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The two-week fair, which started Nov. 13, organized informal
discussions on such topics as reading, speech contests and stamp
collections.
</P>
<P>
For 10 years Guangzhou has carried out many events related to
books and study among young workers.
</P>
<P>
More than two-thirds of city employers such as officials,
managers, technicians and workers in most businesses and
organizations joined the events.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Papermaking Group established a self-study program
among its workers; a reading society in Hualing Refrigerator
Company includes general managers, officials and common
workers. Some reading societies organized by women and migrant
laborers also formed in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
After 20 years of self-study, Rao Huaizu, a technician in
Guangzhou Steel Company, summarized his working experience and
made a few technological achievements which saved his company
several million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city government rewarded workers who
studied well. Departments also adopted measures for financially
stimulating workers to read books and to get diplomas in their
spare time. 
