<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Plans Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an expressway
in south China's Guangdong province, is expected to begin this
year.
</P>
<P>
The 47.5-km expressway from Wushi to Donggang, will be a trunk
of the highway network in eastern Guandong. When it is completed in
1999, it will link up with the Shenzhen-Shantou Expressway.
</P>
<P>
The four-lane expressway is designed for a speed of 100 km per
hour. By 2010, it is expected to be able to handle 44,000
automobiles a day.
</P>
<P>
Construction will be conducted in two stages. The first, a 40-km
section, will cost 1.2 billion yuan.  
</P>
