<HEADLINE> Yunnan University Establishes Humanities College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan University in southwest
China's Yunnan province, which is known for its research on the
Chinese history, has established a Humanities College to improve
research in that area.
</P>
<P>
The 70-year-old university, a major research center for ethnic
groups in China, did a study of ethnic groups in Yunnan in the
1950s.
</P>
<P>
The college has five departments, namely Chinese literature,
news, history, anthropology, and archives, and has doctorate and
post-graduate programs.
</P>
<P>
Lin Chaomin, president of the college, says that they have two
advantages in humanities research: Yunnan has 24 ethnic groups
each with a population of more than 4,000, and 15 ethnic groups
that are unique in the country; and the province borders on some
Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Lin said that his college will begin a large-scale survey of
Yunnan's ethnic groups in near future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
