<HEADLINE> China's NPC Vice Chairman Meets Brunei Sultan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANDAR SERI BEGAWAN, BRUNEI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- China
attaches importance to developing relations with Brunei, Wang
Hanbin, vice chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC) of
China, said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
China is also ready to cooperate on a mutually beneficial basis
with members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations, Wang
said during a meeting with Brunei's acting Sultan and Foreign
Minister Pengiran Muda Mohamad Bolkiah on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who led an NPC delegation, arrived here Monday for a
brief stop-over from the city of Kuching in Malaysia. Wang and his
entourage had also visited Thailand before their tour of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Wang, Mohamad Bolkiah said Brunei pays
attention to developing ties with China and is ready to further
develop bilateral ties.  
</P>
