<HEADLINE> Uganda Captured 10 Rwandans for Robbery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Ten former Rwandese
government soldiers, who have been suspected of robbery along the
Uganda-Rwanda border, have been arrested in Kisoro, south-west
Uganda, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Kiganda, the chief administrative officer of the
district, said police and security forces of the district
launched an operation to arrest the armed thugs.
</P>
<P>
The bandits for a long time used to cross the border between
Rwanda and Uganda to rob local residents at night.
</P>
<P>
The names of the arrested were not available. They are part of
a gang of the bandits, the report added. 
</P>
