<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Consumption Market Improves Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Sales in China's biggest
industrial city steadily increased in October.
</P>
<P>
According to figures issued by the Shanghai Statistics Bureau,
the city's retail volume last month was 11.44 billion yuan (about
1.43 billion U.S. dollars), up 13.2 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's retail volume in the first 10 months of 1997 was
108.7 billion yuan (about 13.5 billion U.S. dollars), up 12
percent over the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
China's National Day on Oct. 1 and the eighth National Games
held recently in Shanghai contributed to the city's consumer sales
for the month.
</P>
<P>
The retail volume of catering in October reached 820 million
yuan, up 26 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, 25,000 color TV sets, 24,000
refrigerators, 18,000 washing machines, and 16,000 air
conditioners were sold in October.
</P>
<P>
Sportswear and appliances for body-building also sold well
during the national games, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
