recent law suspending tax breaks granted to them, an official of
the association said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The association has already drawn up the petition and has been
collecting signatures, said Olga Revina, director of the Ukrainian
League of Companies funded partially by Foreign Investors.
</P>
<P>
"Canceling tax benefits to companies with foreign capital is a
breach of the principle of supremacy of law, and causes serious
damage to the image of the state," the petition says.
</P>
<P>
By approving amendments to the corporate income tax law on
October 23, the Ukrainian parliament finally stripped away foreign
joint venture's rights to tax breaks, which had been suspended
since spring.
</P>
<P>
The legislature made the amendments despite repeated requests
from President Leonid Kuchma that tax relief to manufacturing
joint ventures be restored. 
