<P>
The government forces are now engaged in the third phase of
their operation "Jayasikuru" (Certain Victory), which began in
mid-May to open a land route to the north through rebel-held
territories.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday the forces were able to capture a major junction in
Puliyankulam, a key strategic town on the main highway. Their
immediate task at present is to link the town with Kilinochchi,
which is situated further north.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting with government troops in the north
and east of the country for 14 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
