<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Promotes Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The immediate objectives of
the Kazakh government are the settlement of unpaid pensions and
workers' wages, and reform of the pension system, Akhas Tajutov,
the prime minister's press secretary, said today.
</P>
<P>
Main tasks are to put the state economy on the track of stable
development, and to deepen social reform, especially in the fight
against poverty and unemployment, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tajutov said the government is in great need of cash to promote
reform, to buttress the development of small and medium-sized
businesses, to propel forward fundamental education and to settle
the default on pensions.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months of this year only 86 percent of
state budgetary receipts were accomplished. The Kazakh government
has ordered tax bureaux and customs to improve tax-collecting work
and stop the defaulting on tax payments.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh economy maintained the momentum of picking up this
year with the gross domestic product, gross industrial product and
agricultural product increased by two percent, 3.6 percent and 1.5
percent respectively compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increases to rising oil, ferrous and
nonferrous metal outputs.
</P>
<P>
The new Kazakh government, headed by Prime Minister Nurlan
Utebovich Balgimbeav, started working last month. 
</P>
