<HEADLINE> Nepali Currency Further Devalued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali currency, the
rupee, was devalued today for the fourth time within three months
following the fall of the Indian rupee.
</P>
<P>
The Nepal Rastra Bank today refixed the buying and selling
rates of the greenback at 59.75 and 60.35 rupees respectively from
Tuesday's 58.50 and 59.05 rupees.
</P>
<P>
The central bank of Nepal tried to prop up the currency Tuesday
by floating 13.5 million U.S. dollars at a rate of 1:60 as demand
for the dollar soared amid fears of imminent depreciation of the
Nepali currency.
</P>
<P>
As the Indian rupee fell to a 20-month low against the dollar
Monday, the Nepali rupee, pegged to the Indian currency at a fixed
rate of 1:1.6, has no other way but to follow suit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
