are planning a major attack in Batticaloa, Eastern Province.
</P>
<P>
Security forces in Batticaloa rounded up about 10,000 school
children and checked their identity cards and possessions
following reports that the rebels were disguising themselves as
students in order to infiltrate into the city.
</P>
<P>
Police have also intensified their cordon and search operations
in the area as they found a two-kilogram bomb in a lunch box near
a sentry post.  
