National Electoral Court in order to train military personnel for
the handling, protection and transportation of electoral
materials, which must be taken to each town of the country.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully committed to keeping the election process honest,
because any failure in that task would mean a harsh blow against
democracy, which has been difficult for us to achieve," Hong
Pacheco said.
</P>
<P>
"None of the ballot boxes will be tampered with and, at the end
of the election, all Hondurans will feel thrilled at the turnout
and the results," he added. 
