<HEADLINE> Seized CD Production Lines Begins Producing Authorized CDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen production lines
seized by Chinese officials for manufacturing unauthorized
CDs are now producing legal products, the Press and Publications
Administration announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Since last year China has seized 49 underground CD production
lines, mainly in the southern province of Guangdong, an official
from the administration said. The crackdowns have curbed rampant
copyright infringement, he added.
</P>
<P>
However, the official cited a lack of authorized video and
audio products on the domestic market. To ensure that there will
be a flourishing market that can meet people's demands, the
administration decided to re-open some confiscated production
lines.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that one of the reasons for copyright violations
is that lawful producers cannot meet the demand for CDs.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said all seized productions lines will be sold
to lawful video and audio producers to turn out products which
conform with China's copyright law. 
