<DOCNO> XIE19971119.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "El Nino" to Cause Heavy Drought in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The climatic phenomenon
of "El Nino" will make Brazil suffer the worst drought in the past
34 years from the end of 1997 to the first quarter of 1998, local
press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted Director of the National Weather Institute
Expedito Rebello as saying that the level of the rivers in the
Amazonian region as well as the northeastern region will be
significantly lower than normal times due to shortage of rain.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last week, the Black River, one of the major
rivers in Brazil, lowered some 8.6 meters or more below the normal
level.
</P>
<P>
In the northwestern region, rainfall through the end of this
year to the first three months next year is expected to diminish
nearly 30 percent against the same period one year earlier, when
precipitation was registered at 183 to 216 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
However, in southern Brazil, especially the state of Rio Grande
du Sul, is dashed by heavy rains, which have caused losses of 13
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 90,000 tons of corn crops in the region
will be lost. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971119.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Car Fair to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 100
exhibitors will participate in the 5th International Automobile
Fair, on November 21 to 30 in Santa Fe de Bogota.
</P>
<P>
The Fair will host almost all transnational car makers in the
Colombian market, one of the most attractive markets in Latin
America, according to the Fairs Corporation (Corferias), the
organizer of the event.
</P>
<P>
The automobile sector is one of the few that have enjoyed
remarkable growth this year in Colombia. So visitors will see a
wide range of models and brands, Corferias said.
</P>
<P>
The car industry in Colombia has grown by nearly 30 percent so
far this year. Corferias said the reason might lie in the falling
interest rate, which is good for car sales because many vehicles
are sold under credit. The interest rate has fallen 20 to 24
percent, the lowest in decades.
</P>
<P>
Corferias said the good situation of the industry had brought
to Colombia sophisticated and high-tech car models, with features
Colombians had never seen before.
</P>
<P>
About 90.000 people are expected to visit the Fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
