<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang to Improve Cotton Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, the country's largest cotton producer,
has stored 800,000 tons of high-quality cotton.
</P>
<P>
To increase cotton output and develop more markets, the region
has made great efforts to improve the quality either through
training of cotton farmers and purchasing staffs in local cotton
and linen companies or introduction of planting techniques. More
than 4,400 people in charge of purchasing cotton have received
training.
</P>
<P>
Spreading improved varieties of cotton also has helped farmers
to improve cotton quality.
</P>
<P>
The region's cotton quality was below national standards last
year, causing a loss of more than 100 million yuan (12.5 million
U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
