<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, Albania Sign Agreements on Albanian Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Albania and Italy signed
agreements here today on Albanian laborers in Italy and the
repatriation of Albanian refugees living in Italy.
</P>
<P>
The two agreements were signed by visiting Italian
Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs Piero Fasino, and Albanian
State Secretary for Integration with Europe-Atlantic Maqo Lakrori.
</P>
<P>
Fasino said that under the accords, Albanians would enter Italy
in a planned and orderly way, and the influx of illegal Albanian
immigrants would be effectively controlled.
</P>
<P>
Albanians would only be allowed to work in Italy after they
signed labor contracts and the two governments would decide the
number of Albanians going to Italy annually.
</P>
<P>
Fasino said his government is considering a plan to repatriate
15,000 illegal Albanian refugees who fled to Italy early this year
when a financial scandal plunged the Balkan nation into a
political and economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said the Italian government would continue to help with the
repatriation of Albanian refugees, for which Italy would provide
200 million U.S. dollars to Albania in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Fasino, who arrived today for a one-day visit, also held talks
with Albanian President Rexhep Meidani and Prime Minister Fatos
Nano. He expressed Italy's will to continue helping Albania to
reconstruct its economy and regain its social order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971119.0293 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Hits Nine-month High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Performance of China's economy
was sound in October, said a report issued yesterday by the State
Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The value-added output of China's industry achieved by
enterprises above the township level reached 172.3 billion yuan in
October, up 11.8 percent from the corresponding last year.
</P>
<P>
Value-added output achieved by light industry was 78 billion
yuan in October, up 13.4 percent from the corresponding period
last year. Value-added output achieved by heavy industry was 94.3
billion yuan, up 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The growth rate of light industry was lighter than that of
heavy industry", it said.
</P>
<P>
China's 370,000 enterprises above the township level earned 101
billion yuan in profits in the first nine months, up 30.8 percent
from the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in fixed assets came to 1,061.3 billion yuan in the
January-October period, up 12.1 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales of consumer goods amounted to 2, 150.7 billion
yuan in the January-October period, up 11.4 percent from the
corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
"Economy efficiency of enterprises continued to improve," the
report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
