<HEADLINE> Poland-Latin America Economic Forum Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The First Poland-Latin American
Economic Forum closed today with a number of economic cooperation
contracts.
</P>
<P>
During the forum, Poland signed a steel export contract with
Uruguay, and Colombia inked a flower export agreement with Poland.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Poland signed six letters of cooperative intent
with Latin-American countries.
</P>
<P>
The forum, which was kicked off on Monday, was aimed at
promoting trade and sponsored by the Polish Economic Ministry and
the Association of Latin American Ambassadors to Poland. It
attracted 90 Polish companies and 70 Latin American firms, and
governmental delegates and representatives from Poland and 15
Latin-American countries participated in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the trade volume between Poland and Latin American
countries reached 1 billion U.S. dollars. During the first eight
months this year, it exceeded 600 million dollars. 
</P>
