<HEADLINE> Switzerland to Bid to Host 2004 European Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GEVENA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland will bid to host
the 2004 European Soccer Championships, the Swiss Football
Association (ASF) announced at Zurich on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ASF members along with representatives from Zurich,
Lausanne, Geneva, Berne, Basle and Aarau presented their proposal
at a meeting in Muri.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is home to both the FIFA and UEFA, world and
European soccer governing bodies. The Swiss bid noted that in
2004 FIFA would be celebrating its 100th anniversary in
Switzerland and UEFA its 50th.
</P>
<P>
Spain and Austria-Hungary are the other candidates in the 2004
European Championships bid. 
