the southwestern Greek Peloponnese peninsula and the nearby Ionian
island of Zakinthos, but causing only minor damage to farms and
shops.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 6.6 on the Richter scale occurred at
around 15:12 local time with its epicenter in the sea bed south of
Zakynthos, 290 km southwestern of Athens, the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA) reported Tuesday. (Greece-Earthquake) 
