<HEADLINE> Kwan Withdraws for Foot Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion
Michelle Kwan of the United States decided to pull out of the NHK
Trophy figure skating event due to a foot injury, said the
U.S. Figure Skating Association (USFSA) Tuesday in Colorado
Springs, United States.
</P>
<P>
Kwan, the 1996 world champion, was suffering a minor stress
fracture of the second toe of her left foot before she aggravated
the injury at Skate Canada earlier this month, the USFSA said.
</P>
<P>
Kwan was not expected in the Nagano competition from November
27-30 for a total rest for no less than 10 days with her injured
foot in plaster cast.
</P>
