</P>
<P>
-- The federal government is set to announce plans during the
lead-up to the next election to sell more of Telstra Corp. Ltd.,
the telecommunications giant, following the highly successful
float of the first third of its shares during the last two days.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- The authority of Prime Minister Howard was challenged
yesterday when he was confronted by backbench dissent over his Wik
legislation and was rebuffed on proposed changes to his nursing
home policy.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Treasurer Peter Costello yesterday endorsed a further
selldown of the government's stake in Telstra Corp. Ltd. as the
stock enjoyed a second day of overwhelming investor demand.
</P>
