<HEADLINE> World Bank Provides Loan for Central Bank of Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 20 million U.S. dollar loan as technical assistance for
Brazil' Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized to help Brazil's Central Bank
increase the efficiency of its instruments, particularly in the
area of bank supervision during the next three years and the
application of global consolidated banking supervision as well as
the application of the Core Principles by the Basel Committee for
Banking Supervision that are increasingly gaining worldwide
acceptance.
</P>
<P>
The project is also designed to finance consulting services,
training of personnel and the acquisition of new computer
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The total project cost is estimated at 24.6 million dollars, of
which Brazil's Central Bank will contribute some 4.6 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
