<HEADLINE> Nestle SA Sales Growth Strong in 1st 10 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Sales of Nestle S.A. reached
56.9 billion Swiss francs (about 40.6 billion US dollars) in the
first 10 months this year, announced the Swiss company today at
its headquarters in Vevey.
</P>
<P>
The sales increased 17.5 percent over the comparable period of
1996, Nestle S.A. said at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Growth was particularly marked in Latin America, in the Middle
East and in Southeast Asia. The mineral water business also showed
a very good development.
</P>
<P>
The year-on-year real internal growth accelerated to 3.0
percent after having stood at 2.7 percent at mid-year. Performance
was particularly strong in pet food, beverages and mineral water,
the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
